{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:17.923Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing DataTable's Limits**\n\nI'm now focusing on `DataTable`'s limitations. It has great preset features, but it's rigid. I've realized its reliance on specific keys (like `id`, `name`, etc.) is a major hurdle. Custom actions, as we want them, don't fit its row structure unless we build an entire custom layout; the alternatives are less clear.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Project Panel**\n\nI've shifted focus to a high-fidelity interactive project panel. I'm exploring wrapping React state within `app/admin/projects/page.tsx` for full control over local states. This offers advanced filtering, interactive animations, and a premium layout, meeting UI quality standards. The goal is a custom, self-contained solution without backend dependencies. I'm building a detailed design plan!\n\n\n**Orchestrating AI Delivery**\n\nI'm now conceptualizing the project board as GFF AI's nervous system. It is meant to be an executive flight deck, visually representing sovereign multi-agent integration and enclave rollouts. I'm focusing on the visual metaphor: a deep-space obsidian canvas with technical grids and glowing status indicators. I'm aiming for a dynamic, premium dashboard that orchestrates complex infrastructure, providing key details at a glance. I've designed the header, breadcrumbs, and actions, and I'm planning out the key operational status views.\n\n\n**Defining Project Metrics**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the project board's core deliverables. I've designed a \"+ New Delivery Project\" button, and a metrics ribbon featuring aggregated stats. This will be followed by an advanced multi-filter control deck for refined data control. I'm focusing on the Core Deliverables Ledger, a data table showcasing detailed project info, with custom actions and interactive status modifiers. Also, I'm designing interactive modal overlays for streamlined project creation and status controls.\n\n\n**Implementing Interactive Modifiers**\n\nI'm now integrating instant updates for the Core Deliverables Ledger. I'm focusing on in-line dropdowns or quick modals for immediate status modifications, with internal state updates reflected across counts, tables, and card lists. Also, hover effects and preview workflows enhance the project creation flow. The current update involves animated previews of new project additions, and is focused on mobile responsiveness.\n\n\n\n**Defining Project Boundaries**\n\nI'm now setting clear constraints for the delivery page build. Specifically, I'm avoiding the landing page and existing slug route logic. I'm building with an eye on supported clients, project phases, statuses, and owners, to create accurate and premium filters, with the listed examples guiding the structure.\n\n\n"}}
