{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:25.284Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Admin Interface Design**\n\nI'm now diving into the design of the admin interface at `/admin/projects/page.tsx`, aiming for a Figma-level fidelity experience. I'm focusing on responsiveness, comprehensive search and filtering, and inline updating with a slick creation modal. The challenge lies in translating those feature requests into a simple `AdminProject` structure in typescript, with all those fields: id, name, client, phase, status, owner, nodesCount, enclaveType, and the description.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:27.332Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Populating Mock Project Data**\n\nI've just added the first batch of mock projects to populate the `/admin/projects/page.tsx`. These five initial projects are high-fidelity, matching our themes of sovereign and multi-agent sandbox networks. They are a good start to represent the data to be managed in the admin UI. I've designed each entry to have detailed descriptions, to cover a broad range of data display needs.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:28.694Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Adding More Mock Data**\n\nI've just added two more mock project entries to the dataset. These new entries, labeled \"PROJ-203\" and \"PROJ-204,\" are in addition to the initial five. They're designed to flesh out the `/admin/projects/page.tsx` display with a wider range of data and scenarios. These latest entries have added a deeper layer of potential use cases in the design.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:31.166Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Project Actions**\n\nI'm now focusing on interactive elements. I'm imagining a dark-themed \"Create Project\" button in the page header that triggers a modal. This modal will have input fields for project details, including name, description, client (with dropdown and type-ahead), phase, status, owner, nodesCount, and enclaveType. My goal is a simple, elegant UI for both project creation and status updates.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:32.153Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Implementing Project Actions**\n\nI'm now refining the \"Create Project\" modal, focusing on field validation upon \"Generate and Deploy\". I've planned fields for Phase, Status, Delivery Owner, Nodes Active, and Enclave Mode. The creation should trigger state updates and feedback via a toast. I'm also planning inline status updates: interactive badges for Status and Phase, with popover dropdowns for easy inline editing.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:34.194Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Expanding Interactive Elements**\n\nI'm now integrating an \"Action\" column with a \"Quick Edit\" button for each project, opening a drawer for detailed updates, *plus* interactive status badges for quick inline edits. The layout, aiming for a premium feel, includes an \"Administrative Oversight Panel\" title with a detailed description. We'll have a statistics grid displaying total managed enclaves (with a trend indicator and micro-sparkline) and sovereign delivery phases.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:36.858Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Calculating Project Metrics**\n\nI'm now focused on key project metrics for the administrative dashboard. I'm planning to display the number of projects in \"Production-Live\" or \"Completed\" status. I'll include the count of projects classified as \"At Risk\" or \"Delayed\" under \"Active Security Risks,\" plus a count of active distinct owners on duty as \"Clearance SLA Owners.\" These stats should provide a quick health overview of our projects.\n\n**Designing a Powerful Filter Bar**\n\nI've just designed the filter bar. It begins with a sleek input box with the Lucide `Search` icon for querying project names, IDs, or owners. Dropdown filters are in place for client account, delivery phase, operational status, and delivery owner. There will be a clear \"Reset Filters\" link for when filters are applied. The filter bar is now ready.\n\n**Drafting the Desktop Table**\n\nI've just drafted the structure of the desktop project table. It will feature a clean layout with columns and high-contrast lines. The table's first column, \"Project & ID,\" will display the ID in a small monospace card and the Project Name in bold white text. The second will be a brief project preview description. I'm focusing on ensuring it's easily readable and informative.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:37.982Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Data Presentation**\n\nI'm now focusing on how the data is presented within each table row. For the desktop table, client info is rendered with a `Briefcase` icon and each project's *operational phase* is an interactive pill. I've included a live status indicator with a pulsing dot and plan to include the delivery owner's avatar. I'm prioritizing the display of node details, like the enclave mode and count. The project cards for mobile are in progress as well.\n\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:40.039Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying Navigation Alignment**\n\nI'm now integrating the admin page with existing UI components. I'm checking `components/private-app/navigation.tsx` for layout consistency and any reusable variables. The active tab indicator seems straightforward, automatically activating based on the URL segments, like `/admin/projects`. Now I'm working on robust code for `/admin/projects/page.tsx` and verifying it with linting and building.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:41.363Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Project Actions**\n\nI'm now integrating an \"ExternalLink\" icon within the project table rows. Clicking this will direct users to a detail subpage, identified by the project ID. I'm focusing on the integration of a navigation link to `/admin/projects/[id]`. The focus is a smooth user experience across this feature.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:49:42.668Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Detail Subpage**\n\nI'm now implementing the `/admin/projects/[id]` subpage with detailed project information. The design features a prominent project name and ID, alongside key data points such as client, phase, status, owner, node count, and enclave type. I'm focusing on providing clear and concise visual presentation and responsive design.\n\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
