ing Table Row Styling**\n\nI'm now implementing the `tr` components for each project to refine the display. I'm focusing on hover effects and subtle borders for better visual cues and a premium feel. These components will also incorporate more visual indicators like badges and inline editing capabilities. My goal is a UI that enhances readability and usability.\n\n\n**Adding Project Deprovisioning**\n\nI've successfully added a project deprovisioning functionality, including soft confirmation before removal. The \"ExternalLink\" directs now, just like we discussed, to the details subpage at `/admin/projects/${project.id}`. Inline editing is also on the horizon.\n\n\n**Refining Interactive Table Elements**\n\nI'm now implementing the interactive dropdowns within the table rows for both the status and phase badges. I'm leveraging state management with `openStatusDropdownId` and `openPhaseDropdownId` to manage their appearance. With focused styling, I'm integrating logic to handle and update project information with inline functionality to create a very smooth editing experience.\n\n\n**Refining Interactive Table Elements**\n\nI'm now implementing interactive dropdowns in table rows for status and phase. I'm focusing on seamless state management with `openStatusDropdownId` and `openPhaseDropdownId`. I'm integrating the logic to update project information inline, aiming for a premium edit experience.\n\n\n**Refining Inline Dropdowns**\n\nI'm now styling the interactive dropdowns in the table rows to refine inline status and phase editing. I'm leveraging `openStatusDropdownId` and `openPhaseDropdownId` for state management. I'm also implementing the selection styles and ensuring the updates are seamless. I'm focusing on ensuring it looks and feels like a premium experience.\n\n\n**Refining Desktop Table**\n\nI'm now implementing the `tr` components for each project in the desktop table. I'm focusing on hover effects, borders, and visual indicators. The goal is to improve